If you want to remove the `action` field from domain models, you can store the action separately from the domain models. One way to do this is by creating a wrapper class that holds both the action and the domain model. This way, you can separate the action from the model but still have the necessary information when processing the models.

Here's an example of how you can implement this approach:

1. Create a wrapper class:
```java
public class ModelActionWrapper<T> {
    private String action;
    private T model;

    public ModelActionWrapper(String action, T model) {
        this.action = action;
        this.model = model;
    }

    public String getAction() {
        return action;
    }

    public T getModel() {
        return model;
    }
}
```
